  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      There is an urgent need to engineer targeted physical activity interventions that are&#xD;
      effective and scalable for obese adolescents and young adults (AYA) with type 2 diabetes&#xD;
      (T2D), who often have very low levels of physical activity. The BEAM Trial is a proposed&#xD;
      mobile health (mHealth) intervention that uses behavioral economic-informed financial&#xD;
      incentives and text messaging to promote physical activity in AYA with T2D and prediabetes.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
